        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-03 14:03:25.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2\n\nI'm okay with this since it gets the compile working.  Rootpom had been removed from the <modules> list to break a circular dependency (core pom.xml's parent is rootpom/pom.xml).  The long term fix for this - which I already did in CCSDK - is to move the root pom to its own repository.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "4fc41d6397e4495c7257114092c5a658ab6f914e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1517,
          "name": "Ryan Goulding",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ryandgoulding@gmail.com",
          "username": "rgoulding"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-03 14:08:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> I'm okay with this since it gets the compile working.  Rootpom had\n > been removed from the <modules> list to break a circular dependency\n > (core pom.xml's parent is rootpom/pom.xml).  The long term fix for\n > this - which I already did in CCSDK - is to move the root pom to\n > its own repository.\n\nInstead, why not just have the dependent modules inherit from rootpom instead of core?  Then \"core\" could just be a dumb shell...",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
